{"parse":{"title":"carrot","pageid":41969,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n{{wp}}\n{{wikispecies|Daucus carota}}\n[[Image:Carrot.jpg|thumb|Carrots]]\n\n===Etymology===\n{{dercat|en|qsb-grc}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|karette}} and {{bor|en|frm|carotte}}, both from {{der|en|la|carōta}}, from {{der|en|grc|καρωτόν}}. {{doublet|en|carotte}} and related to {{m|en|caraway}}. Displaced native {{ncog|enm|more}}, from {{ncog|ang|more}}, {{m|ang|moru|t=edible root, parsnip, carrot}}, related to {{ncog|de|Möhre|t=carrot}}.\n* Noun sense of \"motivational tool\" refers to {{m|en|carrot and stick}}.\n* Verb sense in felt manufacture refers to the orange colour of drying furs.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|kâr'ət|a=RP}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈkæɹət/}}\n* {{enPR|kâr'ət|a=GenAm,nMmmm}} {{IPA|en|/ˈkæɹət/}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-ne-carrot.ogg|a=US,nMmmm}}\n* {{enPR|kĕr'ət|a=GenAm,Mmmm}} {{IPA|en|/ˈkɛɹət/}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-carrot.ogg|a=US,Mmmm}}\n* {{rhymes|en|æɹət|s=2}}\n* {{homophones|en|carat|karat}}\n* {{homophones|en|caret|aa=weak vowel}}\n* {{hyphenation|en|car|rot}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q81}}A [[vegetable]] with a [[nutritious]], [[juicy]], [[sweet]] [[root]] that is often [[orange]] in colour, {{taxfmt|Daucus carota|species}}, family {{taxfmt|Apiaceae|family}}, especially the subspecies ''sativus''.\n#: {{syn|en|more<id:carrot><q:obsolete>}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1961|author=Harry E. Wedeck|title=Dictionary of Aphrodisiacs|publisher=The Citadel Press|location=New York|page=42|passage=In general, beets, '''carrots''', and turnips are all of aphrodisiac value in erotic dietary.}}\n# A shade of orange similar to the [[flesh]] of most carrots (also called carrot orange).\n#: {{color panel|ED9121}}\n# {{senseid|en|incentive}} {{lb|en|figurative}} Any [[motivational]] tool; an [[incentive]] to do something.\n#: {{cot|en|stick<id:punishment>}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Coral Davenport; Lisa Friedman|title=Five Decades in the Making: Why It Took Congress So Long to Act on Climate|work=The New York Times|date=2022-08-07|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2022/08/07/climate/senate-climate-law.html|issn=0362-4331|passage=Essentially, lawmakers replaced the sticks with '''carrots'''.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Paul Krugman|title=Climate Is Now a Culture War Issue|date=2023-08-07|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2023/08/07/opinion/climate-is-now-a-culture-war-issue.html|work=The New York Times|passage=In 2022, when the Biden administration finally succeeded in passing a major climate bill, it consisted almost entirely of '''carrots'''—tax credits and subsidies for green energy.}}\n# {{lb|en|UK|slang|derogatory}} Someone from a [[rural]] background.\n# {{lb|en|UK|slang}} A police officer from somewhere within the British Isles, but specifically outside of Greater London.\n# {{lb|en|slang}} A [[redhead]]; a [[ginger]]-haired person\n# {{rfdef|en}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|year=2025|author={{w|Ghostface Killah}}|title=Metaphysics|text=I got the jammy loaded in one hand.<br>Threw a few shots at two '''carrots''' and one jam}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en| white carrot|cuff the carrot|carrot beetle\n|carotane |carotene |carroter |carrotish |carrotwood |rainbow carrots |baby carrot |Camberwell carrot |carrot and stick |carrot bag |carrot cake |carrot cruncher |carrot top |carrotless |carrotlike |carroty |stick and carrot |baby-cut carrot |carrot weevil |carrot-and-stick |carrot-top |carrot-topped |deadly carrot |stick-and-carrot |like peas and carrots |carrot bacon |carrot dog |carrot-nosed |moon carrot |wild carrot |cry carrots and turnips|carrot fly|carrot rust fly\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|fj|kareti|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ms|karot|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|tl|karot|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ta|கேரட்|bor=1|alts=1}}\n* {{desc|th|แครอท|bor=1}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{multitrans|data=\n{{trans-top|''Daucus carota'' ssp. ''sativus''}}\n* Abkhaz: {{tt|ab|ажьаҷыркәа}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|wortel}}\n* Ainu: {{t|ain|フレアタネ|tr=huneatane}}\n* Alabama: {{tt|akz|assikchi laana}}\n* Albanian: {{tt+|sq|karotë|f}}\n* Altai:\n*: Southern Altai: {{tt|alt|моркоп}}\n* Alviri-Vidari: {{qualifier|Vidari}} {{tt|avd|گزر|tr=gazer}}\n* Amharic: {{tt|am|ካሮት}}\n* Apache:\n*: Western Apache: {{tt|apw|bikéghad ágoleʼí}}\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|جَزَر|m}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{tt|arz|جزر|m|tr=gazar}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{tt|acw|جُزَر|m|tr=juzar}}\n*: Libyan Arabic: {{tt|ayl|سفناري|m|tr=sfənnāri}}, {{tt|ayl|سفنارية|m|tr=sfənnāriyya}}\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{tt|ary|خيزو|m|tr=xīzzu}}, {{tt|ary|زرودية|m|tr=zrūdiyya}}, {{tt|ary|جعدة|m|tr=jaʕda}}\n*: South Levantine Arabic: {{tt|ajp|جزر|m|tr=jazar}}\n* Aragonese: {{tt|an|azanoria|f}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{tt|aii|ܓܸܙܵܪܵܐ|m|tr=gizara}}\n*: Classical Syriac: {{tt|syc|ܓܙܪܐ|m|tr=gezzārā}}\n* Arapaho: {{tt|arp|yeneinit}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|գազար}}, {{tt+|hy|ստեպղին}}\n* Aromanian: {{tt|rup|morcuv|m}}\n* Assamese: {{tt|as|গাজৰ}}\n* Asturian: {{tt+|ast|cenahoria|f}}, {{tt+|ast|zanahoria|f}}\n* Avar: {{tt|av|ламадур}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt+|az|kök}}, {{tt|az|yerkökü}}, {{t|az|kəşir}}\n* Baluchi: {{tt|bal|گزرک|tr=gizirk, gazirk}}\n* Bashkir: {{tt|ba|кишер}}\n* Basque: {{tt+|eu|azenario}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|мо́рква|f}}\n* Bengali: {{tt+|bn|গাজর}}\n* Bhojpuri: {{tt|bho|गाजर|m}}\n* Breton: {{tt+|br|karotezenn|f}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|мо́рков|m}}\n* Burmese: {{tt+|my|မုန်လာဥဝါ}}, {{tt+|my|မုန်လာဥနီ}}\n* Buryat: {{tt|bua|морхооб}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|pastenaga|f}}, {{tt+|ca|pastanaga|f}}, {{tt+|ca|carrota|f}}, {{tt+|ca|safanòria|f}}\n* Cebuano: {{tt|ceb|sanahorya}}\n* Central Atlas Tamazight: {{tt|tzm|ⵜⴰⴼⴻⵙⵏⴰⵅⵜ|f}}\n* Chechen: {{tt|ce|жӏонка}}\n* Cherokee: {{tt|chr|ᎠᏓᎵᏥᏍᏗᏍᎩ}}\n* Cheyenne: {{tt|chy|anonévee'tose}}\n* Chichewa: {{tt|ny|kaloti|c1a|c2}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{tt|yue|紅蘿蔔|tr=hung4 lo4 baak6}}, {{tt|yue|胡蘿蔔|tr=wu4 lo4 baak6}}\n*: Dungan: {{tt|dng|хуонлуәбу}}\n*: Hokkien: {{tt+|nan-hbl|紅菜頭|tr=âng-chhài-thâu}}, {{tt|nan-hbl|紅蘿蔔|tr=âng-lâ-pa̍k}}, {{tt|nan-hbl|紅蘿蔔仔|